The paper discusses the use of computational multiagent systems to simulate predator-prey pursuit environments, which falls under the category of multiagent systems (cs.MA). The paper also mentions modifications to predator and prey attributes, which involves artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and control systems (cs.SY). The use of simulation experiments also involves machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper discusses military-relevant scenarios, which could potentially fall under robotics (cs.RO).
